The paper proposes a new model and sampling scheme for hyperspectral images based on the assumption of linear combination of few sources with specific spectral signatures. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and information theory (cs.IT) sub-categories, as it deals with image processing and signal modeling. The paper also mentions the use of sparse models, which is a common topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories. Finally, the paper proposes optimization algorithms and performs experimentation on synthetic and real datasets, which suggests that it may also belong to the signal processing (cs.SI) sub-category.
